      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a concours-level 2002 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Titanium Silver. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS high-pressure stepless variable valve timing system to achieve a breathtaking 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a factory M-variable differential lock. Crucially, this vehicle has undergone proactive rear subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive VANOS overhaul. The suspension geometry remains factory-spec with zero bushing deflection, and the original Style 67 forged alloys are wrapped in fresh Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber. A mechanically pristine example with a documented service longitudinal, free from the typical rod bearing or cooling system vulnerabilities found in lesser examples.",
